If you’re ever around DePaul or Lincoln Park this is a very nice break from the vibe that’s usually around there

Thursday are $5 classic baked potatoes. They're gigantic and absolutely with it. All of the bar and wait staff is very friendly. It's become one of our go to spots.

I've only had two things here so far: the chicken noodle soup (hard pass; it tastes like Campbell's low sodium - bleurgh) and the build your own spud, which was ssssooooo so so so very good. Big, not too dry, seasoned skin, and you can add a cheese, 4 veggies, and a sauce. Also, of note: my server was terrific and the vibe wasn't silent but the music wasn't obnoxiously loud either. Except for that soup, I'll call Lincoln Station a win!

Great place for a Buffalo expat like me to see a game. Beef on weck was added to the menu a while back which was a nice touch.

Decent spot to hang; plenty of beer options and TVs.  Staff is accommodating and hospitable, I recommend checking it out if you want a decent spot to meet friends and chill.  Just misses out on 5 stars due to limited menu but food is good, so if you can find something you like, you'll probably enjoy it.
Love this place.  The tortilla soup is my favorite.

Overall experience was good . Clean atmosphere,  friendly staff.  Quality of food was decent, but it took longer than expected to get our food.  Staff could have been more attentive. Will likely return.

Lots of good memories of this place back in the day (late 90s) and just visited tonight w s bunch of chorus members who all loved the place.

Solid place to grab some food and drinks. Wasn't amazing or anything but service was good. Drinks were a bit expensive but that's the city for ya. Whenever I show up with a big group I judge how well they handle my ridiculous friends and we were well taken care of! Would definitely go back
Good atmosphere prices was reasonable and employees is quick and courteous
Great food and a great place to watch Sports.

This is the best Buffalo Bills backer bar in Chicago. I've watched many games here while eating some authentic wings and drinking Blue Light drafts. The bar does tend to fill up before game time, so I recommend arriving an hour before kickoff.

Split the Spinach Artichoke Dip and LS Burger. Spin-Dip was amazing, homemade pita chips we're delicious and perfect. Burger was good, would probably try a different sandwich next time. Fries were housecut and very good. Definitely worth going to again.

The atmosphere is great and it never felt crowded on any of the days I went. Free pool, normal drink choices, and I haven't tried the food. Great place to shoot some pool (two red felt 8 footers, decently maintained. Good house cues, chalk, and hand chalk by request)  Will definitely be back, and it's a block from my friend's apartment.
Good beer selection, good food. FYI: It does fill with college students as the evening progresses - neither good nor bad, but if you do not want that to be your experience, then now you know.
Good selection of ales, decent food, good atmosphere!

go to hood spot. Food and drinks great. good draft selection. pool in the back

Lincoln Station is definitely worth stopping by if you're in the neighborhood. It's a solid bar with above average tap selection and above average bar food. I'm not sure it's at the level of a destination to travel to from a far away neighborhood, but if you're in the area I'd definitely recommend stopping in.

Cool place for drinks and Pub grub directly across from the legendary Biograph Theater where Dillinger was shot. The food was quite tasty and the drinks were well priced. Not too crowded either.
They have a fantastic beef on weck. Good atmosphere. Not very crowded on a Friday night. You'll be examined by tourists on the John Dillinger tours if you sit on front.
Great food and service and large beer selection. Perfect way to chill on a Sunday afternoon with friends and family

We went on Monday when they have 50 cent wings and really good beer for $3. The waitress was really quick-witted when she invited me to a free beer as they forgot to order 4 of my wings. It´s not a big amount of money but the good attitude of the waitress made the difference. Therefore 5 stars.

My mom and I came here together, and the bartender Emily was so friendly! They have specials everyday on food and/or drinks, so I'd definitely look that up. I remember Monday was 40 cent wings, Tuesday was dollar tacos, and Wednesday was $5 burgers w/ fries. Half price appetizers everyday from 4-6 PM!! Would definitely come again.

Love this place for lunch or dinner. Beers are always perfectly chilled and they have a pretty good BLT.  Great bar to just hang out with some friends.

Fun place, we play pool there fairly often. Food is pretty good, for a bar.
Had a lot of fun watching the CHICAGO CUBS playing in the world series at this place good food good service and the beer wasn't bad either.
Great service, great beer, great food, and great prices. A welcome oasis in Lincoln Park.
Free pool on Thursday!

Great bartenders and great food.  Eclectic whiskey and bourbon collection.  Come play pool or darts in a large backroom.  Bar does not have the feel of the rest of the Lincoln Park neighborhood. Calmer.  Way more chill and fun atmosphere.  Huge big screen and TVs everywhere for game days as well.
Good drink/food specials. A nice place to hang out and grab a drink with friends.
Our place to go!
Staff was great, they played the game on the big projector upon request. Good bar food too!
Nice place to grab some drinks and play a bar game. Reasonable prices and nice staff.

I've done the rounds of bars in Chicago and this is one of my favorite. Not an A+ in the atmosphere/memorability department, but hits on all the important things: GREAT beer selection, good bar food, prices that won't break the bank (especially for college students), and very clean. Not one of those places where you feel out of place wearing jeans and a tee - easy to relax, love going here with just a friend or medium sized group.
The $1 gourmet sliders on Wednesday are amazing! They are small but are juicy and have good flavor.  Amazing weekday specials and a fun place to play pool too!
Great deals on every night. Also a great selection of local brews. And they have cheap pool!

(Translated by Google) Happy Friday bar every Friday, incredible selection of Midwest beers in the United States. Very nice employees and garcons. Best stuffed potato in Chicago! Very special place to relax and have a cold beer!  (Original) Bar com happy hour todas as sextas-feiras, variedade incrivel de cervejas do Midwest nos Estados Unidos. Empregados e garcons muito legais. Melhor batata recheada de Chicago! Lugar muito especial para relaxar e tomar um cerveja gelada!
Good place to go for food and drinks.  Food is pretty good for bar food---definitely recommend their spuds.  Good bar for a drink in Lincoln Park.

This place always has a great beer list. It's in the neighborhood so we visit often. Their food is decent. I am definitely getting a baked potato next time, they always look delicious, but their wraps, burgers and salads are good too.
Great craft beer and best prices on the area.  Their baked spuds are awesome.
Good service and good people. This place is depressing though. I've never walked out of a bar more happy in my life than I have been after leaving this place.
